
// This Hyperlambda code snippet saves the content of a stream to a file. It uses the [io.stream.save-file] slot to write the stream's content to the file path specified by the [.filepath] node. The stream is retrieved from the [file] node within the [.arguments] node using the [get-value] slot.
io.stream.save-file:x:@.filepath
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/file/*/stream
